OUSEPH VARGHESE V. JOSEPH ALEY & ORS [1969] INSC 185 (18 August 1969)

 18/08/1969 
ACT:
 Specific Relief Act 1877 (1 of 1877), s. 12--Suit for specific performance of oral agreement to re-convey property sold through sale-deed-Burden of proof on plaintiff is heavy--Court will rarely grant specific performance of contract, on the basis of oral evidence only--Offer by defendant in written statement to sell part of property to plaintiff at certain price--Offer not accepted by plaintiff--Court can not pass decree in favour of plaintiff on the basis of such offer--Costs where both parties have withheld facts from Court.
 
